.START 

Intek Diversified Corp. said that Anglo York Industries Inc., which holds about 40% of the company's common stock, is considering making a $2-a-share tender offer to acquire an additional 12%. 

In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Intek shares were quoted at $1.75 bid, up 12.5 cents. 

Intek said that Anglo York hasn't made a final decision whether it will go ahead with the tender offer.
Intek is a holding company with interests in coating products for static control, and is also a maker of electrostatic simulation and testing equipment. 

